4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, an individual who holds a
6 municipal office may not serve on a municipal planning
7 commission.
8 This bill would remove the prohibition against a
9 municipal official from serving on a municipal planning
10 commission.
11 Under existing law, local authorities may be
12 incorporated to provide water, sewer, and fire
13 protection services under the direction of a board of
14 directors, and individuals serving as a state or local
15 official may not serve on the board of a water, sewage,
16 or fire protection authority.
17 This bill would remove the prohibition against a
18 municipal official from serving on the board of
19 directors of a local water, sewer, or fire protection
20 authority.
21
22
23 A BILL
24 TO BE ENTITLED
25 AN ACT
26
27 Relating to local commissions and authorities; to amend
28 Sections 11-52-3, 11-52-14, and 11-52-15, Code of Alabama
