200 "§11-52-15
201 A Class 6 municipality with a council-manager form of
202 government may provide by ordinance for the members of the
203 municipal planning commission, upon the expiration of the
204 current term of office for the current members, to be
205 appointed by the city council in lieu of appointment in the
206 manner provided in Section 11-52-3; provided, that the mayor
207 or his or her designee shall be a voting member of the
208 planning commission and the mayor shall appoint all remaining
209 members of the planning commission subject to approval by the
210 city council.
